timeline.summary: An automatic reply email was sent from the Victim Witness Coordinator (EFTA00037992) to an unknown recipient regarding an external email concerning Ghislaine Maxwell. The email indicates the sender was out of the office returning on January 21, 2020, and directs recipients to email for immediate assistance.

Sigrid McCawley received an indemnification action filed by Maxwell in USVI, contradicting previous depositions where she claimed Epstein did not assist with her legal bills or receive any value. The document references previously unproduced correspondence and lists companies she was allegedly employed by. ABC is reportedly doing a story on this information. James E. Hill sent a warning regarding the external email and its confidential nature.

Sigrid McCawley received an indemnification action from a reporter filed by Maxwell, referencing contradictory statements to previous depositions regarding Jeffrey Epstein and her relationship with him. The action includes previously unproduced correspondence and lists companies she was purportedly employed by. James Hill sent an email alerting Sigrid McCawley to the document and cautioning about the external email.

On July 29, 2020, Sigrid McCawley of Boies Schiller Flexner LLP notified a recipient about a filing by Ghislaine Maxwell’s counsel in the case *v. Maxwell* (Doc# 1078, S.D.N.Y. 1:15-cv-07433-LAP). The filing was a letter from Ty Gee requesting reconsideration of Judge Preska’s July 23 ruling, accompanied by five exhibits (Exhibits A-E). The email included a warning about external emails and a disclaimer regarding confidential information.

An email chain alerts the recipient to a new document filed in the case of Ghislaine Maxwell (Doc# 1078, S.D.N.Y. 1:15-cv-07433-LAP). The document is a letter from Ty Gee requesting reconsideration of a court ruling, dated July 29, 2020. Exhibits A through E are attached to the filing. The email also includes standard legal disclaimers regarding confidential information and external email cautions.

An email was sent on August 27, 2020, requesting confirmation of spellings before issuing subpoenas to three chefs who worked for Jeffrey Epstein. The email details the subject as external subpoenas and includes sender, recipient, and CC information.

An Assistant United States Attorney from the Southern District of New York requested a call to discuss a witness related to an incident detailed in the attached document, “2020-04-10 Unterview_302.pdf”. The email was sent on September 23, 2020.

An email was sent on October 5, 2020, regarding a warrant (2020-06-26,_search_warrant,_20_mag_6719.pdf) associated with case EFTA00038029. The email was flagged as “Normal” importance and was an external email.

An email exchange, dated October 20, 2020, between an individual from the FBI (NY) and the USAHUB-USAJournal111 regarding a review of a “Maxwell discovery” external email. The email chain included a message named “JEXTERNAL_EMAILL_RELMaxwell_discovery_review.msg” and the subject line "RE: [EXTERNAL EMAIL] - RE: Maxwell discovery review”. The recipient of the email was EFTA00027075.

An email was forwarded from [REDACTED] to [REDACTED] on October 22, 2020, regarding a call with SDNY concerning discovery and the Epstein investigation. The email was marked as FYI and contained an unnamed attachment labeled "EFTA00038287".

An email was sent on October 22, 2020, from an unknown sender to an unknown recipient regarding a call concerning discovery related to a case involving Jeffrey Epstein and the SDNY (Southern District of New York). The email was marked as “Normal” importance and had no attachments.

An email was sent from [REDACTED] to Bee ("USAHUB-USAJournal111") regarding an accepted call with SDNY concerning discovery and the Epstein investigation. The email included a message titled "Call w/ SDNY re: discovery, Epstein investigation." The email was sent on October 22, 2020, and addressed to EFTA00029142.

An email was sent on October 22, 2020, from an unknown sender to an unknown recipient, subject to a call with Sony regarding a discovery and an Epstein investigation. The email is attached as EFTA00029143.

On October 23, 2020, at 3:00 PM UTC, there was an external email call with SDNY regarding discovery and the Epstein investigation. The call lasted 30 minutes. The event was classified as X-PERSONAL and created on October 22, 2020. It had a priority of 5 and a DTSTAMP of 2020-10-22 16:34:21 +0000.

On October 23, 2020, at 3:00 PM GMT, an external email call took place regarding discovery and the Epstein investigation, categorized as X-PERSONAL. The event was created on October 22, 2020, with a priority of 5.

On October 23, 2020, at 15:00:00 +0000, a call occurred regarding discovery and the Epstein investigation, involving an external email. The event was marked as X-PERSONAL priority 5 and created on October 22, 2020, at 23:35:24 +0000. A reminder was set to display a message 15 minutes prior to the start. The sender’s email address is redacted. EFTA00038289 is also listed.

An email was sent from [REDACTED] to [REDACTED] regarding a follow-up, forwarded from an unknown sender. The email’s subject line is “[EXTERNAL EMAIL] - FW: Follow up” and its message-id is <88789ce3-b399-4186-b521-13d95ec0e6fe@fbi.gov>. The email is related to case EFTA00026573.

An email exchange concerning a review of a "Maxwell discovery" occurred between multiple individuals, including those associated with the FBI and USAHUB-USAJournal111. The email thread originated from an unknown sender and involved recipients at [REDACTED] and [REDACTED]. The message contained an attached email with the subject "RE: [EXTERNAL EMAIL] - RE: Maxwell discovery review".

Brittany Henderson sent an email with a client list (EP_Client_List_DOJ.pdf) to FBI agents in New York. Bob is also sending a list of clients. The email chain originated from an external email and was forwarded by the sender.

An email exchange between “Bee” (USAHUB-USAJouma1111) and an unknown recipient regarding an external email titled “[EXTERNAL EMAIL] - RE: Ghislaine Maxwell Triggerfish.” The email was sent on December 28, 2020, and included an attached message named “REJEXTERNAL_EMAIL_-_RE:_Ghislaine_Maxwell_Triggerfish.msg.” The email is identified as EFTA00015878.

On February 16, 2021, at 11:37 AM EST, a user from ICE-ISLIP, HSI ASAC accessed record P3N06596100A01 (Jeffrey Epstein) via the Person Lookout Query, triggered by a query hit (TECSID: P3N06596100A01). The request originated from ICE and was sent through donotreply@cbp.dhs.gov.
An email was sent from [REDACTED] to review Maxwell physical evidence related to file EFTA00038583. The email included an attachment named “unnamed”.

On 2021-03-31, an external email review regarding Maxwell Physical Evidence took place between 15:30:00 and 21:00:00 GMT. The event was classified as X-PERSONAL, created on 2021-03-30, and assigned a priority of 5. The identifier for this event is EFTA00038584.

A client, represented by Mariann Wang, requested cancellation of a meeting due to repeated discussions about interactions with Jeffrey Epstein and a belief that their information wouldn't materially advance ongoing prosecutions. The email was sent to [REDACTED] with a copy to Gloria Allred.

On April 2, 2021, at 3:04 PM EDT, a user named Ghislaine Maxwell accessed record EFTA00037746 through a Person Lookout Query initiated by TASPD. The access occurred at CBP-HQ, OFO NAIL TARGETING CTR, using TECSID criteria.

An external email was sent from [REDACTED] to [REDACTED] with CC’d recipients [REDACTED]. The subject was "Maxwell team call" and was sent on April 23, 2021, at 22:37:57 +0000. The email is attached as EFTA00038600.

An external email meeting, designated "Maxwell team call," took place on April 26, 2021, from 19:00:00 to 20:00:00 GMT. It was organized under a "X-PERSONAL" classification, created on April 23, 2021, and had a priority of 5. A reminder was set to display a message 15 minutes before the start.

On 2021-04-29, at 14:00:00 +0000, an external email meeting was canceled for a “Hold for Maxwell witness meetings.” The meeting was scheduled from 14:00:00 to 15:30:00 +0000 and was classified as X-PERSONAL with a priority of 5. The record was created on 2021-04-29 02:11:22 +0000 and last modified at the same time. The attendee was EFTA00038599.

This document pertains to a redaction analysis regarding the case *US v. Maxwell*, specifically concerning external email correspondence regarding photo and discovery deficiencies. The email was sent on May 3, 2021.

An email thread concerning the case *US v. Maxwell*, specifically regarding photo and discovery deficiencies, originated from [REDACTED] and was sent on May 3, 2021. The email is identified as EFTA00038595.

An email was sent from [REDACTED] to [REDACTED] regarding the case *US v. Maxwell*, specifically concerning photo and discovery deficiencies. The email was dated May 3, 2021, and referenced an external email with the subject “RE: [EXTERNAL EMAIL] - RE: US v. Maxwell - [conferral re photo and other discovery deficiencies]” (identified as EFTA00038596).

An external email was sent from NYPD/FBI’s Child Exploitation Human Trafficking Task Force to [REDACTED] and [REDACTED], with CC to [REDACTED]. The email subject was “Trial Subpoena,” dated May 12, 2021, and included a trial subpoena attachment.

An email chain discusses obtaining account documentation related to Financial Trust Co. accounts, specifically concerning a transfer to Maxwell on 10/19/99 and identifying the source of funds. The sender requests account statements, Bates numbers, and any KYC documents associated with the accounts.  A signature card for the JP Morgan account ending in 5001 is specifically requested and not found within the production.
An external email was sent on July 12, 2021, from [REDACTED] to [REDACTED], with CC’d to [REDACTED], regarding a court subpoena (attached as 2021.07.12_Court_Subpoena_EFTA00038688).
An external email was sent on July 21, 2021, from EFTA00038701 to an unknown recipient. The email included two attachments: “Epstein_Blackbook.pdf” and “USGME01088970_(masseuse_list).doc”.

An external email was sent from [REDACTED] to [REDACTED] regarding the administration of the Maxwell Juror Questionnaire. The email was sent on August 27, 2021, at 23:03:51 +0000, and is attached as EFTA00038683.

An external email was sent from [REDACTED] to [REDACTED] regarding the administration of a Maxwell Juror Questionnaire. The email was sent on August 27, 2021, with the subject “EXTERNAL EMAIL - Maxwell Juror Questionnaire Administration” and the file identifier EFTA00038685. Two redactions are present on page 1.

An email was sent to multiple recipients regarding Amazon return records for the “Maxwell Amazon Records” case. The sender, an Assistant United States Attorney, requested a copy of the returns. Attached were two zip files – “Original Returns” and “SDNY_GM_00000966-976 (Amazon)” – containing original and Bates stamped versions of the returns, respectively, accessible via a Box link. The Bates stamped files were provided to facilitate easy review due to their non-password protected status.

An email chain, dated September 21, 2021, and October 7, 2002, discusses a subject titled "This is fun," including mentions of Ghislaine Maxwell and a website, wowmail.com, offering free email services. An attachment related to EFTA00038719 is also referenced.

On October 9, 2021, an Assistant United States Attorney from the United States Attorney’s Office, Southern District of New York, sent emails to a “SANYS” individual and “Inca” containing documents related to the Epstein investigation. The attachments included: a search warrant document dated June 20, 2020; an email status update regarding external emails related to Epstein evidence dated August 4, 2020; High Definition (HD) files dated October 9, 2020; and a document detailing evidence pulling from the Bronx dated October 9, 2020.

On October 12, 2021, [REDACTED] sent an email to [REDACTED] regarding spreadsheets, potentially related to trial exhibit material. The email was forwarded by Byrne, who advised [REDACTED] that he had been asked to inquire about the spreadsheets. El requested the spreadsheets be delivered by the following morning, including a phishing warning within the email.

An email was sent on October 28, 2021, containing scanned copies of a black book and yellow pages of notes. The attachments were “black book174042.pdf” and “yellow_pages173901.pdf”. The email subject was “[EXTERNAL EMAIL] - Scanned black book & yellow pages of notes.” The file identifier is EFTA00038863.

An external email event, designated EFTA00038686, involved the administration of a Maxwell Juror Questionnaire. It occurred between November 4, 2021, 04:00:00 +0000 and November 6, 2021, 04:00:00 +0000 at the 40 Foley Courthouse. The event was classified as X-PERSONAL and created on August 27, 2021. A reminder was set to display 18 hours prior to the start.

An email was sent from EFTA00038945 to request updated tracking spreadsheets for Maxwell and Epstein’s tipline/hotlines. The spreadsheets, allegedly from the FBI and dating back to last summer, were attached to a previous email from [REDACTED] and [REDACTED]. EFTA00038945 requested a call to discuss the request the following day.

An email exchange discusses obtaining information regarding potential witnesses for a case involving child exploitation, human trafficking, and the NYPD/FBI/FBI Task Force. The sender requests DOBs, approximate ages, identities, reasons for testifying, and locations of six witnesses (listed numerically 1-6). The email also includes a cautionary note about external email attachments and phishing. A United States Attorney is also involved, referencing the Southern District of New York.

On November 12-13, 2021, an external email event, designated EFTA00038684, occurred at the 40 Foley Courthouse. The event involved the administration of a Maxwell Juror Questionnaire and was classified as X-PERSONAL with a priority of 5. A display message was scheduled to appear 18 hours prior to the start date, and a reminder was also created.

Bobbi Sternheini sent an external email regarding the case *U.S. v. Maxwell S2* (20 Cr. 330 (MN)). The email included a courtesy copy of an ECF filing (Defense_Reply_to_Dkt_350.pdf; ATT00001.htm) and was sent to Christian Everdell, Laura Mennin, and Jeff Pagliuca.

The email chain discusses scheduling a call between individuals, including an Assistant Special Agent in Charge, Assistant United States Attorney, and potentially others. Multiple PDF documents (EFTA00010241 and EFTA00010242) are attached and referenced for discussion. There are warnings about external emails and the need to protect sensitive information.

Bobbi Sternhei sent an external email regarding the U.S. v. Maxwell S2 case (20 Cr. 330 (AJN)). The email attached a courtesy copy of an ECF filing titled "Response_to_Govt_voir dire_opposition.pdf" and an HTML document (ATT00001.htm). Christian Everdell, Laura Mennin, and Jeff Pagliuca were included in the “To” field.

Bobbi Sternheim sent an external email to Christian Everdell, Laura Menninger, and Jeff Pagliuca regarding the filing “10-27 It to Court.pdf” in the case US v. Maxwell S2 20 Cr 330 (MN). The email included a courtesy copy of the ECF filing.

Bobbi C. Sternheim sent an external email to multiple recipients regarding the U.S. v. Maxwell S2 case (20 Cr. 330 (AJN)). The email included a courtesy copy of an ECF filing and her updated contact information. It also contained a standard disclaimer regarding confidential and privileged information within the message and attached documents. A redaction was noted on page 1.

Bobbi C. Sternheim sent an external email to multiple recipients regarding the U.S. v. Maxwell S2 case (20 Cr. 330 (AJN)). The email included a courtesy copy of an Electronic Filed Communication (ECF) filing and her updated contact information. The email also contained a standard confidentiality and disclaimer notice regarding the contents of the message and attached documents.

Christian Everdell of Cohen & Gresser LLP sent an external email to [REDACTED], Jeff Pagliuca, and Laura Menninger regarding a Defense Rule 16 disclosure. The email included attachments related to the disclosure, specifically redacted documents including: a letter to the government, certifications from AT&T and FedEx, a list of certified FedEx invoices, Interlochen Records, a redacted A. Farmer Release, and an Epstein NPA. A confidentiality notice and privacy policy link were also included.

On December 17, 2021, an Assistant United States Attorney contacted Theresa Acosta, the court reporter for a Maxwell deposition, due to her unavailability due to her father’s hospitalization. The U.S. Attorney requested a subpoena be sent for her testimony and requested she attend the courthouse at lunch to be available for the deposition. Contact information for Theresa Acosta was provided, including her phone number and email address. A security warning about external emails was also included.

Allison Stoddart from WilmerHale sent an external email to JPMorgan Chase regarding a production being sent via FIR. The email attached a letter and included the production password. She requested notification of any access issues and reiterated the confidentiality of the email and attachments.

An email was sent from [REDACTED] to [REDACTED] on January 3, 2022, with the subject "EXTERNAL EMAIL." The email contains a link to a Daily Mail article about Ghislaine Maxwell and a victim asking questions about being haunted. The email’s purpose is FYI.

On January 14, 2022, Judge Alison J. Nathan scheduled Ghislaine Maxwell’s sentencing for June 28, 2022, at 11:00 a.m. The Court delayed preparing a presentence investigation report until April 2022 and maintained the existing schedule for briefing on the new trial motion and other post-verdict motions. The Government was instructed to indicate by January 18, 2022, whether it seeks an exclusion of time under the Speedy Trial Act for the perjury counts, along with the basis for that request.

An external email chain discusses sketches created during the Maxwell trial. Elizabeth Williams is seeking originals or prints of the sketches she and her partner were sketched during. She inquired about the sketches with a sender who was available to discuss options and potentially obtain the originals. The email chain also includes a reference to a "Mittlig galconst" and a note about arguments underway in a federal case involving Maxwell, potentially related to the Sarah Paint trial.

On March 8, 2022, from 15:00 to 18:30, there was an external email regarding a hearing for Ghislaine Maxwell. The hearing was to take place in Courtroom 110, 40 Foley. Attendees were required to complete a COVID-19 questionnaire and wear an N95, KN95, or KF94 mask within the courthouse. Failure to comply with these protocols would result in removal from the courthouse. The hearing was ordered by Judge Alison J. Nathan on March 3, 2022.

The document records an external email regarding the sentencing of Ghislaine Maxwell. The sentencing was scheduled for June 28, 2022, at 11:00 a.m. with Judge Alison J. Nathan. The court delayed preparing a presentence investigation report until April 2022. The government was required to indicate by January 18, 2022, whether it sought an exclusion of time under the Speedy Trial Act for the perjury counts.

On November 30, 2022, at 07:40:22 EST, a user named Ghislaine Maxwell accessed a record (EFTA00037010) at the ICE-WILLISTON Bulk Cash Center via the Person Lookout Query, using TECSID criteria. The request originated from ICE.

An external email event, titled “In re Epstein: FBI [REDACTED] Video Review,” took place on 2023-05-23 from 20:00 to 21:00 at Patterson Belknap, organized by Ruzumna and Daniel. The event was classified as X-PERSONAL. Lauren Doxey was a listed attendee. A reminder message was to be displayed 15 minutes before the start. The email contains privileged/confidential information with specific handling instructions. EFTA00038996 is also referenced.

An email was sent from [REDACTED] to [REDACTED] and [REDACTED] regarding an external bail opinion (2020.12.28_20cr330_Opinion_&_Order_re_bail.pdf). The opinion contained no redactions and was attached.

An email was sent from [REDACTED] to [REDACTED] regarding a review of a recent bail submission. The sender, Detective from the NYPD FBI Child Exploitation Human Trafficking Task Force, requested a meeting with the recipients to discuss the submission, offering options for communication including phone, video conference, or an in-person meeting at the office. Alternative dates of tomorrow or Friday were also suggested. The case file number is EFTA00038522.

An Assistant United States Attorney requests that someone contact Theresa Acosta, the court reporter for Maxwell’s deposition, to be available at the courthouse for lunch to potentially witness the defense’s agreement to a stipulation. Mandy has Acosta’s number.
